                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15311371" author="ndimiduk" created="Wed, 1 Jun 2016 23:37:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Shouldn&apos;t a publicly-visible Apache repository be for official releases?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15311376" author="dimaspivak" created="Wed, 1 Jun 2016 23:41:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So my thoughts were that we can reserve the simply-named tags for official releases, but then take liberties with longer tag names for our use if it means simplicity in pushing and pulling images (and document the difference extensively). e.g. &lt;tt&gt;docker pull apache/hbase&lt;/tt&gt; could pull down a Docker-ized version of the latest HBase repo, but &lt;tt&gt;docker pull apache/hbase:centos6.6_branch1.2&lt;/tt&gt; could grab down the image needed for testing of distributed clusters in Docker.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15311437" author="dimaspivak" created="Thu, 2 Jun 2016 00:14:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Or perhaps we have both? Let me reach out to Apache Infra to see if we can have access to the public Docker Hub creds to push our releases and a separate less-public registry for testing stuff.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15311452" author="dimaspivak" created="Thu, 2 Jun 2016 00:22:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Adding link to INFRA JIRA.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15346414" author="jfarrell" created="Thu, 23 Jun 2016 13:18:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;push to dockerhub is handled by automated build off of the github mirror on push. To enable all that is needed is the path in the repo where the Dockerfile is located if not at the top level &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15425339" author="dimaspivak" created="Wed, 17 Aug 2016 20:44:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Docker Hub images are for automated builds only. Now trying to find out where to push the images we&apos;re creating pre-release on a thread to infra@...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15425416" author="jfarrell" created="Wed, 17 Aug 2016 21:32:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the ASF bintray would probably be the best place for that, I can setup HBase for that if you would like&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
